TORCH014 [*] Avoid `torch.tensor(...).to(device)`; pass `device=` to `torch.tensor()` instead
  --> TORCH014.py:10:6
   |
 9 | # Single positional device string
10 | x1 = torch.tensor([1.0]).to("cuda")
   |      ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
11 |
12 | # Device keyword
   |
help: Move device into `torch.tensor()` call
7  |
8  |
9  | # Single positional device string
   - x1 = torch.tensor([1.0]).to("cuda")
10 + x1 = torch.tensor([1.0], device="cuda")
11 |
12 | # Device keyword
13 | x2 = torch.tensor([1.0]).to(device="cuda")
note: This is an unsafe fix and may change runtime behavior

